Your privacy is important to us. It is our policy to respect your privacy regarding any information we may collect from you across our website.

## Information we collect

### Log data

When you visit our website, our servers may automatically log the standard data provided by your web browser. This data is considered “non-identifying information”, as it does not personally identify you on its own. It may include your computer’s Internet Protocol (IP) address, your browser type and version, the pages you visit, the time and date of your visit, the time spent on each page, and other details.

### Personal information

Our website currently does not ask for personal information, such as your name and email address. The only personal information we collect is what you voluntarily provide to us via our contact form. This information is used solely for the purpose of responding to your inquiries and is not stored on our servers.

## How we use your information

We use the information we collect in various ways, including to:

- Provide, operate, and maintain our website
- Improve, personalize, and expand our website
- Understand and analyze how you use our website
- Develop new products, services, features, and functionality

## Cookies

We do not use cookies for tracking purposes. If cookies are used on our site, they are used solely for important functions, such as to ensure that the website works properly.

## Security

The security of your personal information is important to us, but remember that no method of transmission over the Internet, or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.

## Changes to this policy

At our discretion, we may change our privacy policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected here, so we encourage you to visit this page regularly. We will also notify our users of any changes to our privacy policy.

